text"},{"code":"withDiscardingTaskGroup(returning:body:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Don’t use a task group from outside the task where you created it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In most cases,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the Swift type system prevents a task group from escaping like that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"because adding a child task to a task group is a mutating operation,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and mutation operations can’t be performed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from a concurrent execution context like a child task.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Refer to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/TaskGroup","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" documentation for detailed discussion of semantics shared between all task groups.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Discarding-behavior","level":3,"text":"Discarding behavior"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A discarding task group eagerly discards and releases its child tasks as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"soon as they complete. This allows for the efficient releasing of memory used","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by those tasks, which are not retained for future ","type":"text"},{"code":"next()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" calls, as would","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be the case with a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/TaskGroup","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Cancellation-behavior","level":3,"text":"Cancellation behavior"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A discarding task group becomes canceled in one of the following ways:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"when "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/DiscardingTaskGroup/cancelAll()","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is invoked on it,"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"when the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Task","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" running this task group is canceled."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since a ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiscardingTaskGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a structured concurrency primitive, cancellation is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automatically propagated through all of its child-tasks (and their child","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tasks).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A canceled task group can still keep adding tasks, however they will start","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"being immediately canceled, and may act accordingly to this. To avoid adding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"new tasks to an already canceled task group, use ","type":"text"},{"code":"addTaskUnlessCancelled(priority:body:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than the plain ","type":"text"},{"code":"addTask(priority:body:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which adds tasks unconditionally.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For information about the language-level concurrency model that ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiscardingTaskGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is part of,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https://docs.swift.org/swift-book/LanguageGuide/Concurrency.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"identifier":